 of this award research is broadly defined to include all paradigms of scholarly endeavor with particular emphasis on empirically based research this award recognizes individuals who have received a terminal degree in their discipline or profession within the past seven years dr mitchell who completed her doctoral work in september 2005 is being recognized for her impact on community engagement research and practice through her influential work exploring race in service learning civic identity and critical service learning the service learning initiative in csre began in 2007 through a generous grant from the raikes foundation the initiative prioritizes an integrated model of service learning that emphasizes mutual benefit creating meaningful service opportunities that provide tangible outcomes for community organizations and powerful learning experiences for students csre typically offers seven service learning courses each year as director of service learning tania works closely with course faculty to develop partnerships coordinate logistics and share pedagogical strategies another key aspect of our service learning initiative is the community research summer internship program which tania also directs this program prepares and supports students to engage ethically and effectively in research experiences designed for and with a community agency or organization the opportunity to study race and ethnicity through community engagement is a unique aspect of csre's academic program and tania's work has brought the center national attention as a leader in service learning and community engagement 2010 stanford university the center for comparative studies in race and ethnicity stanford california 94305 650 723 2244 terms of use stay connected
